page.title: 14TENTERDEN HIGH STREET
page.content: In Tenterden High Street it is very busy, especially when you go to school. The only problem is that people park their cars every where. Quite a few of the shops like the Gallery Book Shop are old. At half term we go to the market and one day we went up the St. Mildred's church tower and took a photograph of it. On the field next to the recreation ground there are sometimes fairs or the circus. On the recreation ground we have swings, a slide, climbing frame,and a see-saw on which we can play all the rest of the year. On Saturdays during the winter the Tenterden Football Club play matches on the field next to the rec. The Cricket Club play at Small-hythe and there is a 9 hole golf course on the Woodchurch Road.
